{
  "stem": "19895.8",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 307.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The border which I knew from concentration camp, I am crossing it now the other direction.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Russians freed me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I am ironically leaving the Russian-dominated Hungary to go to the west.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I arrive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And successfully crossing the border, not an easy task, and arrived to Vienna, where I start to make contacts with people whom I wanted to try to get contact with.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I had a little address book with me and the physician handbag.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that was my all, my positions.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I contacted in Vienna some international relief organizations, including a Jewish relief organization.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were already having thousands and thousands of Hungarian refugees crossing the border.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I contacted a young boy who my mother talked a lot about, who she met in Sweden when the Swedish Red Cross took her to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This boy came with a school group to cheer them up and entertain them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And was a very personable young boy, who just kept returning to this group of Hungarian Jewish Holocaust survivors, and apparently learned Hungarian language from them to the point that my mother said he spoke unbelievably well.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, why do I tell about this?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because it just happens to be so that I met him in the United States here later, when he took residence in America.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when my parents joined me in the United States, my mother had a chance to see him again.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was like, she was like a mother to him as well, because this was a fantastic story that this boy seen mother when she was just a barely-alive Holocaust survivor in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and that's a side part of the story.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
